01. Simple registration
    % ngsi -fg -reset
    % curlTest reg firstReg 
    
    Check that all is in DB.

	EXPECTED RESULT:
    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
      <registerContextResponse>
        <registrationId>1339680125T001</registrationId>
      </registerContextResponse>
------------------------------------------------------------------
02. Check that data is recovered/found in DB on restart
    - kill ngsi process and run the same command again

	% killall ngsi
	% ngsi -fg  # don't reset the database ... !
    % curlTest reg firstReg
    - should fail as we cannot register an entity twice ...

	EXPECTED RESULT:
    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
      <registerContextResponse>
        <registrationId>1339680174T001</registrationId>
        <errorCode>
          <code>404</code>
          <reasonPhrase>already exists</reasonPhrase>
          <details>Entity 'ConferenceRoom', type 'Room' already exists in a 'Create' Request</details>
        </errorCode>
      </registerContextResponse>
------------------------------------------------------------------
03. Simple recovery
    % curlTest disc simpleDiscovery
    - make sure you see 'temperature' as only attribute

    EXPECTED RESULT:
    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
      <discoverContextAvailabilityResponse>
        <contextRegistrationResponseList>
          <contextRegistrationResponse>
            <contextRegistration>
              <entityIdList>
                <entityId type="Room" isPattern="false">
                  <id>ConferenceRoom</id>
                </entityId>
                <entityId type="Room" isPattern="false">
                  <id>OfficeRoom</id>
                </entityId>
              <entityIdList>
              <contextRegistrationAttributeList>
                <contextRegistrationAttribute>
                  <name>temperature</name>
                  <type>degree</type>
                  <isDomain>false</isDomain>
                  <metaData>
                  </metaData>
                </contextRegistrationAttribute>
              </contextRegistrationAttributeList>
              <registrationMetaData>
              </registrationMetaData>
              <providingApplication>http://192.168.100.1:70/application</providingApplication>
            </contextRegistration>
          </contextRegistrationResponse>
        </contextRegistrationResponseList>
        <errorCode>
          <code>200</code>
          <reasonPhrase>Ok</reasonPhrase>
          <details>No problem</details>
        </errorCode>
      </discoverContextAvailabilityResponse>
------------------------------------------------------------------
04. Adding attributes to an entity
    % curlTest reg firstRegAddPressureToConferenceRoom <REGISTRATIONID>
    - make sure the attribute 'pressure' is added to 'ConferenceRoom', and not to 'OfficeRoom'

    EXPECTED RESULT:
    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
      <registerContextResponse>
        <registrationId>1339680125T001</registrationId>
      </registerContextResponse>

------------------------------------------------------------------
05. Changing values of metadatas of an attribute, belonging to an entity
    % curlTest reg firstRegChangecm2ForOfficeRoom <REGISTRATIONID>

	EXPECTED RESULT:

