06. Add an entity that already exists
    % curlTest reg firstReg
    - make sure no new identical Entity is added

	EXPECTED RESULT:

------------------------------------------------------------------
07. Updating two entities with different Registration IDs
    % curlTest reg firstReg2
    - Now you have ConferenceRoom and ConferenceRoom2, but as they were created at
      different occasions, their RegistrationIDs are different so, the following should fail:
    % curlTest reg updateFirstReg1and2

	EXPECTED RESULT:

------------------------------------------------------------------
08. Updating an entity with bad Registration IDs
    % curlTest reg firstRegAddPressureToConferenceRoom notTheCorrectRegId

	EXPECTED RESULT:

------------------------------------------------------------------
09. Updating an entity with NO Registration ID
    - This is exactly the same thing as 'Trying to create an Entity that already exists' (case 06)
    - Which is OK, just that if no new attribute is added, nor any of its metadatas,
      nothing will be done ...

	EXPECTED RESULT:

